Thanks for the up but these are bad crops w/below average video quality. One also finished before the end of the Ep.

@FX5:

The long list of links on RLSLOG suggests this is good enough until the scene does it tonight:

http://www.rlslog.net/human-target-2010-s02e09-e10-ws-dsr-xvid-err0001/#comments

As for bad cropping, the "A" channel and the "Space" channel here do not yet broadcast in HD. The content was 16:9 but was formatted as 4:3. Therefore there was black on the top and the bottom. For whatever reason, the "14+" at the top and the A channel logo at the bottom extended into this black area. I think that cropping out the black parts was the best choice.

As for quality, I agree. But I didn't claim it was great quality - quite the contrary.
